::::::{{DIcon|Talk}} Regarding your people, the Mountain Dwellers...
:::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504038404-->
:::::::'''Petros:''' ...Curious about, Georios' people, you are first.
:::::::'''Petros:''' Born with dromases. Cradle, crowded.
:::::::'''Petros:''' Kephale gave, humans wisdom and resilience. Cerces gave, creations only wisdom. By Georios' time, little left.
:::::::'''Petros:''' Georios gave us, lot of earth, making us tall and strong. We talk with, our arms.
:::::::'''Petros:''' Still, we are mocked. No good jobs. Some became, blacksmiths. Others just iron blocks. We praise Kephale, praise Talanton. We are now guards.
:::::::'''Petros:''' We envy dromases. They have wisdom. At least, more than us.
